thout work, all life goes rotten. But when work is soulless, life stifles and dies.', 532, 0), (440400, 'Because I have work to care about, it is possible that I may be less difficult to get along with than other women when the double chins start to form.', 1739, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (440401, 'The idea of having a steady job is appealing.', 2185, 0), (440402, 'And if small businesspeople say they made it on their own, all they are saying is that nobody else worked seven days a week in their place. Nobody showed up in their place to open the door at five in the morning. Nobody did their thinking, and worrying, and sweating for them.', 66572, 0), (440403, 'Work alone is noble.', 3061, 0), (440404, 'Big pay and little responsibility are circumstances seldom found together.', 1187, 0), (440405, 'We work to become, not to acquire.', 4, 0), (440406, 'Your chances of success are directly proportional to the degree of pleasure you desire from what you do. If you are in a job you hate, face the fact squarely and get out.', 14083, 0), (440407, 'Life grants nothing to us mortals without hard work.', 2542, 0), (440408, 'When a work lifts your spirits and inspires bold and noble thoughts in you, do not look for any other standard to judge by: the work is good, the product of a master craftsman.', 5879, 0), (440409, 'When more and more people are thrown out of work, unemployment results.', 4110, 0), (440410, 'As an actor, to have achieved financial stability is amazing. But I always have this weird fear that I''m not going to get any more work; it''s about not having enough money.', 70611, 0), (440411, 'For the last several years and culminating in six months in orbit next year, I''ve been training for my third space flight. This one is almost in a category completely different than the previous two, specifically to live in on the space station for six months, to command a space ship and to fly a new rocket ship.', 2061, 0), (440412, 'I work to stay alive.', 13058, 0), (440413, 'I think about my work every minute of the day.', 70612, 0), (440414, 'Concentrate on your job and you will forget your other troubles.', 5249, 0), (440415, 'There is no disgrace in working. There was no silver spoon around at the time I was born.', 55096, 0), (440416, 'The biggest job we have is to teach a newly hired employee how to fail intelligently. We have to train him to experiment over and over and to keep on trying and failing until he learns what will work.', 66718, 0), (440417, 'My husband changed jobs so fast that I simply never knew what business he was in.', 66690, 0), (440418, 'If Botticelli were alive today he''d be working for Vogue.', 2206, 0), (440419, 'If you put all your strength and faith and vigor into a job and try to do the best you can, the money will come.', 13165, 0), (440420, 'Part of the way the work world works is not so much creating a separation between your work and your free time, but creating the illusion of a separation between your work and your free time. Every day is the weekend for me, which means I''m always busy.', 34875, 0), (440421, 'Most people treat the office manual the way they treat a software manual. They never look at it.', 69527, 0), (440422, 'You''re blessed if you have the strength to work.', 18404, 0), (440423, 'I''m working myself to death.', 70613, 0), (440424, 'Be open to the amazing changes which are occurring in the field that interest you.', 70448, 0), (440425, 'On any given day, my father wasn''t likely to return from work before I was asleep for the night. I saw that a man''s work was important, that he must pursue it tirelessly, and that it might require certain sacrifices, like being away from the warmth and comfort of home.', 69159, 0), (440426, 'I work 338 days a year, 16 hours a day.', 5963, 0), (440427, 'You know, I think the greatest gift in the world is a good employee, you know, or people who can do your work for you and do it well the way you''d like to have it done. And I''ve always been able to surround myself with really good people.', 54882, 0), (440428, 'One thing I never want to be accused of is not working.', 68857, 0), (440429, 'The harder you work... and visualize something, the luckier you get.', 70614, 0), (440430, 'Married couples who work together to build and maintain a business assume broad responsibilities. Not only is their work important to our local and national economies, but their success is central to the well-being of their families.', 70615, 0), (440431, 'And to get real work experience, you need a job, and most jobs will require you to have had either real work experience or a graduate degree.', 70616, 0), (440432, 'Put off thy cares with thy clothes; so shall thy rest strengthen thy labor, and so thy labor sweeten thy rest.', 4935, 0), (440433, 'Management must manage!', 66617, 0), (440434, 'Managers in all too many American companies do not achieve the desired results because nobody makes them do it.', 66617, 0), (440435, 'There''s something to be said in favor of working in isolation in the real world.', 7259, 0), (440436, 'After two weeks of working on a project, you know whether it will work or not.', 70035, 0), (440437, 'I can''t imagine anything more worthwhile than doing what I most love. And they pay me for it.', 70617, 0), (440438, 'It can be liberating to get fired because you realize the world doesn''t end. There''s other ways to make money, better jobs.', 70618, 0), (440439, 'I always got my work done before playing.', 69790, 0), (440440, 'Work expands so as to fill the time available for its completion.', 61019, 0), (440441, 'Honest labor bears a lovely face.', 18697, 0), (440442, 'Work is a prayer. And I start off every morning dedicating it to our Creator.', 70619, 0), (440443, 'America believes in education: the average professor earns more money in a year than a professional athlete earns in a whole week.', 18694, 0), (440444, 'Let us realize that: the privilege to work is a gift, the power to work is a blessing, the love of work is success!', 3996, 0), (440445, 'Two months after I got out of test pilot school, I saw an advert that said NASA was recruiting more astronauts. The best job you could have as a test pilot was being an astronaut, so I volunteered.', 70620, 0), (440446, 'Anyone who can walk to the welfare office can walk to work.', 10909, 0), (440447, 'As I understand it, sport is hard work for which you do not get paid.', 59066, 0), (440448, 'The economy in the Valley will need to grow if students want to come back and work with their specialized degrees. We need to develop more to create more opportunities.', 70621, 0), (440449, 'I met an American woman and got married so I had to get a job.', 70622, 0), (440450, 'There is a vast world of work out there in this country, where at least 111 million people are employed in this country alone - many of whom are bored out of their minds. All day long.', 66574, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (440451, 'The world''s most famous and popular language is music.', 67110, 0), (440452, 'The American Dream is a term that is often used but also often misunderstood. It isn''t really about becoming rich or famous. It is about things much simpler and more fundamental than that.', 66707, 0), (440453, 'If you are a leader, you should never forget that everyone needs encouragement. And everyone who receives it - young or old, successful or less-than-successful, unknown or famous - is changed by it.', 1810, 0), (440454, 'The name Muhammad is the most common name in the world. In all the countries around the world - Pakistan, Saudi Arabia, Morocco, Turkey, Syria, Lebanon - there are more Muhammads than anything else. When I joined the Nation of Islam and became a Muslim, they gave me the most famous name because I was the champ.', 1751, 0), (440455, 'Acting is not about being famous, it''s about exploring the human soul.', 68256, 0), (440456, 'America is known as a country that welcomes people to its shores. All kinds of people. The image of the Statue of Liberty with Emma Lazarus'' famous poem. She lifts her lamp and welcomes people to the golden shore, where they will not experience prejudice because of the color of their skin, the religious faith that they follow.', 28287, 0), (440457, 'In the future, everyone will be famous for 15 minutes.', 321, 0), (440458, 'I''ve always strived to be successful, not famous.', 100, 0), (440459, 'Pleasure without God, without the sacred boundaries, will actually leave you emptier than before. And this is biblical truth, this is experiential truth. The loneliest people in the world are amongst the wealthiest and most famous who found no boundaries within which to live. That is a fact I''ve seen again and again.', 4001, 0), (440460, 'Glory is fleeting, but obscurity is forever.', 1702, 0), (440461, 'If you want to be a rock star or just be famous, then run down the street naked