 ought to give the waiter another dollar?''', 53024, 0), (440481, 'I''m bored with that line. I never use it anymore. My new line is ''In 15 minutes everybody will be famous.''', 321, 0), (440482, 'When someone becomes successful or rich and famous, people perceive that person as being different. But I''m the same guy I''ve always been.', 70626, 0), (440483, 'The scientists I looked up to at the beginning were not Latino. They were famous scientists of many years ago, like Madame Curie. Later, I realized that there were also, but a very few, Latino scientists. There were good ones, but very few, because there wasn''t as much a tradition to be a scientist in our culture. But this is changing.', 70566, 0), (440484, 'I was definitely not the kid that just wanted to be famous for no reason whatsoever and then happened to find comedy. Fame and all that stuff have always been slightly terrifying to me, and it makes me very anxious.', 2383, 0), (440485, 'Don''t worry about writing a book or getting famous or making money. Just lead an interesting life.', 824, 0), (440486, 'In the beginning, I loved being famous, but now I am tired of it and I would like to go back to my freedom.', 70627, 0), (440487, 'I''m more interested in being good than being famous.', 58263, 0), (440488, 'To be famous, in fact, one has only to kill one''s landlady.', 532, 0), (440489, 'People think being famous is so glamorous, but half the time you''re in a strange hotel room living out of a suitcase.', 67882, 0), (440490, 'When you become famous, being famous becomes your profession.', 70628, 0), (440491, 'Martyrdom is the only way a man can become famous without ability.', 1304, 0), (440492, 'Celebrity is the chastisement of merit and the punishment of talent.', 91, 0), (440493, 'We all want to be famous people, and the moment we want to be something we are no longer free.', 1780, 0), (440494, 'For a time, at least, I was the most famous person in the entire world.', 16509, 0), (440495, 'Fame is the thirst of youth.', 62558, 0), (440496, 'I imagined being a famous writer would be like being like Jane Austen.', 28, 0), (440497, 'Public misbehavior by the famous is a powerful teaching tool.', 47187, 0), (440498, 'The whole celebrity culture thing - I''m fascinated by, and repelled by, and yet I end up knowing about it.', 7852, 0), (440499, 'Celebrity means that I can affect people in a positive way.', 67705, 0), (440500, 'It''s really easy to avoid the tabloids. You just live your life and don''t hang out with famous people who are in the tabloids. Don''t do anything controversial and be a normal person. Have friends. And get a job and keep working.', 69265, 0);
