to accommodate me and make me more money, make me more famous and get me more girls.', 60154, 0), (440913, 'I remember I wanted to be an athlete. I wanted to be in the NFL or NBA or something, and I don''t think I dreamed of being a benchwarmer. I''m sure I wanted to be the best. But I didn''t really ever think I was going to be a famous musician.', 60154, 0), (440914, 'I wanted to be the most famous. And it wasn''t until I hung out with Justin Bieber that the whole thing got demystified. The mystique of it was gone.', 60154, 0), (440915, 'You know, many people who become famous and enjoy great success when they''re young disappear after that. Maybe I''ve lucked out because I came back and went to work.', 70631, 0), (440916, 'What happened to me during the last couple of years of ''The Partridge Family'' was I became so famous and so isolated and so unhappy that I had to do anything I could to end it.', 70631, 0), (440917, 'Nobody prepares you for what happens when you get famous, and I didn''t handle it well.', 67037, 0), (440918, 'I''m willing to make compromises based on someone I think is the one, but I think it''s psychologically important to people when they''re famous to be the only famous person they know.', 861, 0), (440919, 'I had no desire to be famous I just wanted to make the greatest music ever made. I didn''t want anyone to know who I was. ', 68214, 0), (440920, 'Don''t call me famous, but it''s hard to be out with my friends now.', 69734, 0), (440921, '''The Narrow Road to the Deep North'' is one of the most famous books of all Japanese literature, written by the great poet Basho in 1689.', 9692, 0), (440922, 'I''d always need a creative outlet. But sometimes, I do fantasize what my life would be like if I weren''t famous.', 63992, 0), (440923, 'It''s key to become ''famous'' for one thing first, and that will give you the credibility to go into other areas once your ready... which generally means a long time and a lot of perfecting!', 67039, 0), (44