ne famous. So my relationship with fame is not bedazzled.', 36782, 0), (441034, 'I got the famous Oprah hug!', 69198, 0), (441035, 'Barack Obama is the most famous living person in the history of the world.', 68451, 0), (441036, 'There''s such big pressure on people who are incredibly famous, on those who have people sitting outside their front door and taking photos every time they move.', 68452, 0), (441037, 'I know I had my equivalents in Adrian Lester and Lenny James when I was at drama school. I remember David Harewood doing ''Othello'' at the National, and Adrian Lester having done Cheek by Jowl''s famous ''As You Like It and Company'' at the Donmar. Not necessarily performances I saw, but just the fact they happened was massively encouraging.', 70676, 0), (441038, 'People are getting famous now for serving food out of a truck, or for, well, pork buns. I don''t know if I''m really pleased to be a part of that. I''m somewhat terrified of what the future holds, especially in America.', 69049, 0), (441039, 'I was thinking about it: so many of my stories are about my family life, not about being related to a lot of famous people. That''s my grandma, that''s my mama, my daddy, my aunt, my uncle, my stepdaddy. I''d probably tell them even if they weren''t well known.', 70677, 0), (441040, 'I hear the way people talk about the children of famous people. They''re not treated very well. The presumptions are usually quite awful. So I tried to establish myself with a couple of movies. After ''Juno'' I thought: ''I think I''ve defined myself enough as my own director that I''d love to work with my father.''', 37737, 0), (441041, 'I was a latchkey kid, so when I saw the ''Lifestyles of the Rich and Famous,'' that showed me that there was a different type of lifestyle out there. I was curious about it and amazed about it.', 68280, 0), (441042, 'I''m not a very good impersonator, my friends maybe, but not famous people.', 70263, 0), (441043, 'I''ve been very, very lucky in my career, in my life - from day one. When aspiring directors say, ''What''s your advice?'' first I say, ''Be born the son of a famous director. It''s invaluable.''', 37737, 0), (441044, 'The stones themselves are thick with history, and those cats that dash through the alleyways must surely be the ghosts of the famous dead in feline disguise.', 405, 0), (441045, 'Famous people complain about fame, but they never want to give it back, myself included.', 405, 0), (441046, 'I became very famous, as a teenager, and my name and photo were splashed in all the media. They made me larger than life, so I wanted to live larger than life, and the only way to do that was to be intoxicated.', 61043, 0), (441047, 'I used to be like everyone else and think the Kardashians are just famous for being famous. But I''ve been really impressed with how supportive Kim Kardashian has been of Caitlyn Jenner.', 67062, 0), (441048, 'I have a great job writing for ''The Office,'' but, really, all television writers do is dream of one day writing movies. I''ll put it this way: At the Oscars the most famous person in the room is, like, Angelina Jolie. At the Emmys the huge exciting celebrity is Bethenny Frankel. You get what I mean.', 1289, 0), (441049, 'I was a guy who wanted to become famous. There was steam coming out of my ears, I wanted to be famous so badly. You want the attention, you want the bucks, and you want the best seat in the restaurant. I didn''t think what the repercussions would be.', 68455, 0), (441050, 'If I hadn''t had the experience of being famous, I would have searched for it my whole life. I would have just gone on and on trying to find it.', 68455, 0);
