amous Viners used the song, and that was crazy because I had never been a part of something like that. I drank champagne for the first time when it got 100,000 plays.', 69359, 0), (441143, 'Nothing in life prepares you to be famous.', 1491, 0), (441144, 'Although I was born to famous parents, I know and feel the problems of ordinary citizens.', 70690, 0), (441145, 'The thing that most critics miss about Faulkner is that his famous storytelling voice is, in fact, a standard Southern storytelling voice that is typical of the Gulf Coast - Mississippi, Alabama and so on.', 17617, 0), (441146, 'When I was a kid, I would come home from school, and my mom would buy the industrial-size Famous Amos cookies or Chips Ahoy when I was lucky. And I would sit in front of the TV set with a glass of milk... and I would dump cookies in there, smash them with my spoon, and eat cookies and milk with a spoon watching ''The Dukes of Hazzard.''', 67634, 0), (441147, 'I know really, really famous people who are terrified every time they walk on to a stage.', 70267, 0), (441148, 'I''m not famous for my back story investigations I''m lucky that I work with good writers and it''s usually in the script. ', 70267, 0), (441149, 'I loved cowboy films and TV series, and I learned bits of English from them. My favorite was ''Laramie'', with Robert Fuller and John Smith. I used to watch ''The Lone Ranger'', which had been famous in Japan as well. I idolized these cowboys.', 458, 0), (441150, 'I feel like everyone has the right to privacy, even if you''re the most famous person in the world.', 68466, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (441151, 'I didn''t even listen to any music until I was 19, really. I just wanted to be famous. But I didn''t say it to anyone because I was really embarrassed at the thought.', 68466, 0), (441152, 'The Kardashians can be famous for being famous. What do they do? I can''t figure it out.', 10298, 0), (441153, 'Bill Cosby is a famous black guy who has a bully pulpit the size of the world; it''s global. He puts his colossal foot on the vulnerable necks of poor people, and as a result of that, we don''t have a balanced conversation.', 3861, 0), (441154, 'Never, never have a famous partner. It''s too complicated.', 18322, 0), (441155, 'I grew up with a pretty tough mom. She was a self-appointed neighborhood watchdog, and if she saw that any of the local boys were up to no good, she would scold them on the spot. Although she is only 5 feet 2, she was famous in our neighborhood for intimidating men three times her size and getting them to do the right thing.', 28478, 0), (441156, 'Fame necessarily isn''t really tied to success at all. Fame is just being recognized for doing what you do, whether it''s good or bad. Osama bin Laden was famous.', 58634, 0), (441157, 'There''s the famous thing that the A&R man from the record company is supposed to do: He''s supposed to come into the studio and listen to the songs you''ve been recording and then say, ''Guys, I don''t hear any singles.'' And then everybody falls into a terrible depression because you have to write one.', 27000, 0), (441158, 'I think basically becoming famous has taken the place of going to Heaven in modern society, hasn''t it? That''s the place where your dreams will come true. It''s an act of faith now; they think that''s going to sort things out.', 27000, 0), (441159, 'As a shy kid growing up in Sheffield, I fantasized about how it would be great to be famous so I wouldn''t actually have to talk to people and feel awkward. And of course, as we all know