gely unvisited and in silence. The gardeners tend the lawns, one section at a time. Even at the famous sites, tourism is inconstant.', 564, 0), (441271, 'You have to pretend that your life is a financial pleasure even when your autographs are bouncing.', 3584, 0), (441272, 'When I was younger, I used to say, One day I''ll be famous.', 60478, 0), (441273, 'I love the urban comedies, because they keep you famous, keep you having fun, and keep you in love with the business. Those are my roots. I''ll always love doing those.', 25037, 0), (441274, 'It wasn''t until after I became famous that people noticed I played in the NFL. I kind of snuck in!', 25037, 0), (441275, 'My famous line is ''Product is king.''', 70711, 0), (441276, 'Bruce Lee was very famous. I watched his movies and he is amazing. He is a martial arts master, his philosophy, his movement, both physically and mentally, were very strong.', 3939, 0), (441277, 'Although I''m not an orphan and I can''t lift a horse. I was, however, briefly famous for my feats of strength: at about age 11, I could competitively arm-wrestle a full-grown man.', 2479, 0), (441278, 'No one can train you to be famous. How do you deal with the loss of anonymity, the loss of privacy? You have to be disciplined.', 68971, 0), (441279, 'The first syndicating I tried was when two partners and I created a production company in 1952. We wanted to syndicate famous Bible stories and sell them for $25 a show.', 70712, 0), (441280, 'I''d wanted to be famous for as long as I could remember.', 68492, 0), (441281, 'If somebody for some reason, for music or for movie, becomes famous, it''s because they have something, something special.', 70627, 0), (441282, 'The press attack people to sell more papers without thinking, but when you get famous you have to put up with this kind of stuff.', 70627, 0), (441283, 'When you''re in a relationship with a very famous person, you have to make compromises.', 70713, 0), (441284, 'I never wanted to do biography 