er me. But he wouldn''t come up to me and say, ''Hi Dave!''', 68555, 0), (441361, 'Being famous before you''ve formed your personality, before you have that self-esteem, is dangerous.', 62310, 0), (441362, 'When you''re a famous, successful person at 16 years old, the rules change for you. Everybody is doing things for you to make life easier so you can go out and play. And I think you miss out on lot of growing up and a lot of reality checks.', 62310, 0), (441363, 'I had a flight trainer who is one of the biggest and most famous helicopter pilots the world.', 70746, 0), (441364, 'I seek no longer to be a ''famous'' person, and instead I wish to live a ''normal'' life.', 42965, 0), (441365, 'When I''m living in the world of luxury and celebrity, which is where I found myself for a large part of my life, it''s a walk-on part. Not a vital necessity, like it is for so many people. I enjoy it but I can see right through it!', 70747, 0), (441366, 'I don''t know if any famous people follow me, but their daughters definitely do.', 70748, 0), (441367, 'I''m not the guy that wants to be famous and make loads of money and sell loads of records. I don''t want that. I just want to be true. I want to be... I want to serve music. I want to be honest.', 22702, 0), (441368, 'I never wanted to be rich or successful or famous. I just wanted to be happy and have fun.', 26908, 0), (441369, 'I think success right now is not about how famous you are or how much you''re getting paid, but it''s more about if you''re steadily working and you''re happy with what you''re doing.', 68395, 0), (441370, 'If you ever get rich and famous, by definition you are special. You have done something special, and therefore you start to behave special. Then if the floor drops out, and you become down and out, you have a really new perspective.', 70749, 0), (441371, 'The seven wise men of Greece, so famous for their wisdom all the world over, acquired all that fame, each of them, by a single sentence consisting of two or three words.', 63015, 0), (441372, 'Living in L.A., everyone likes to mold you and change you. I don''t care about fame, I don''t care about being a celebrity. I know that''s part of the job, but I don''t feed into anyone''s idea of who I should be.', 66826, 0), (441373, 'If there''s anything more mortifying than being famous at 14, it''s being washed up right after.', 43686, 0), (441374, 'For famous men have the whole earth as their memorial.', 16758, 0), (441375, 'Fame is a lot of pressure, especially when you''re responsible for your entire family. Financially, emotionally - everything.', 22992, 0), (441376, 'I would be a huge hypocrite if I didn''t tell you that at one time in my life I thought the way that you made music was you got on a major label and you got famous.', 70750, 0), (441377, 'Stardom can be a gilded slavery.', 4743, 0), (441378, 'I''m just not a private person. It''s not like I do things because I want things to be public; it''s just that''s my way of expressing myself, and I happen to be very famous.', 26719, 0), (441379, 'Celebrity, to me, is not a thing to seek.', 70751, 0), (441380, 'Celebrity gives us delusion of self importance.', 70752, 0), (441381, 'My wife, she is so good. She was a famous singer - had a show in Carnegie Hall, did a big city tour for RCA. Then she made the mistake of marrying me. The next year, another tour, but the third year, she had Mario and said, ''Either I''m a mother or a singer.''', 70753, 0), (441382, 'For somebody famous, it''s weird anyway to meet someone, because they have a preconceived notion of who you are.', 70754, 0), (441383, 'I''ve been around some very famous people, but no one has the effect Maradona has; people tremble in his presence.', 70755, 0), (441384, 'Why does anybody want to be famous? You know what''s important to me? Having lunch! Pasta! Seeing my friends! Is that so crazy?', 70756, 0), (441385, 'Rich and famous is not bad, but poor and famous sucks.', 70757, 0), (441386, 'I